title: Yadanarbon F.C.
text:
Yadanarbon Football Club ( ) is a Burmese professional <a href="association%20football">football</a> club based at the <a href="Bahtoo%20Stadium">Bahtoo Stadium</a> in <a href="Mandalay">Mandalay</a>. The club was a founding member of the <a href="Myanmar%20National%20League">Myanmar National League</a> in 2009. In the first round of the 2017 domestic league season, Yadanabon FC drew a home attendance of 4,000, the highest in that round.
Honours.
It is the winner of the league's first two cup competitions: the <a href="MNL%20Cup%202009">MNL Cup 2009</a> and the <a href="MNL%20Cup%202009-10">MNL Cup 2009-10</a>.
